<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Thayer</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 26.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23, 1863</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of September 5, No. 37, has
                            been received. The information it communicates relative to the cotton
                            crop in Egypt, and the favorable progress of the Suez canal enterprise,
                            is very interesting and instructive.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William S. Thayer</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Alexandria.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>